## README

    Welcome to Connect4, a classic two-player connection game implemented in C++. This game is a digital version of the popular board game where players take turns dropping colored discs into a vertically suspended grid. The objective is to be the first to form a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal line of four of one's own discs.

    - Features
        A text-based user interface.
        Two-player gameplay on the same machine.
        Colorful console output for better visibility and game experience.
        Checks for valid inputs and full columns.
        Evaluates winning conditions after each move.

## Usage

   - Run make in the extracted directory, and then a ./playgame to execute the output file
   - Alternatively, you can also just run the make run command in the directory.

Have Fun!!
